SEC Sues Washington Woman for $135 Million Ponzi Scheme

-- B y   G r e g   C h a n g
-- 
2011-09-22T20:58:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/sec-sues-washington-woman-for-135-million-ponzi-scheme.html
 Doris E. Nelson, the owner of a
Spokane, Washington-based payday loan business, was sued by the
Securities and Exchange Commission over a $135 million Ponzi
scheme.  Nelson raised about $135 million between 1999 and 2008 from
at least 650 investors in the U.S.,  Canada , and  Mexico , the
agency said in a statement on its website.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Greg Chang at 
 gchang1@bloomberg.net  